{
  "slug": "as-of-july-2026-financial-and-bankruptcy-status-of-6c2b2dbf",
  "query": "As of July 2026, financial and bankruptcy status of these companies: Chegg Inc, America's Car-Mart Inc, JetBlue Airways, Peloton Inc, Faraday Future Intelligent Electric, Petco Health and Wellness. Which are at highest risk of bankruptcy filing in mid-2026? Any going concern warnings, debt maturities, or restructuring news?",
  "answer": "I've completed the research. Here's the summary of findings:\n\n## Bankruptcy Risk Ranking (as of July 14, 2026)\n\n**Highest risk — explicit going-concern warnings, September 2026 deadlines:**\n\n1. **America's Car-Mart (CRMT)** — $3.11. The clearest pre-bankruptcy setup. Explicit going-concern doubt, FY2026 net loss of $139.1M (-$16.79/share), defaults already waived under a June 19, 2026 lender amendment (Silver Point) running through early Sept 2026. Has hired **Houlihan Lokey and FTI Consulting** and explicitly lists **Chapter 11** among its options.\n\n2. **Faraday Future (FFAI)** — $0.16. Recurring going-concern doubt; pre-revenue ($512K/quarter) with continuous cash burn. Facing **Nasdaq delisting** with a Sept 16, 2026 compliance deadline; survives only on dilutive raises.\n\n**Moderate:**\n\n3. **Chegg (CHGG)** — $0.85. Discrete $33.9M convertible maturity on Sept 1, 2026, but appears **covered by ~$67.9M cash**. No formal going-concern warning; risk is business erosion (revenue -48% YoY), not an imminent solvency cliff.\n\n4. **JetBlue (JBLU)** — $5.35. Credit-distressed (Fitch CCC+, S&P B-, Moody's B3), Q1 2026 loss -$319M, >$500M cash burn — but ~$2.2B cash + ~$6.5B unencumbered assets and **no maturity wall until 2029**. A *mid-2026* filing is unlikely; it's a 2027+ story.\n\n**Lowest risk — refinanced, cash-generative:**\n\n5. **Petco (WOOF)** — $2.55. Refinanced to **2031**; EBITDA-positive.\n\n6. **Peloton (PTON)** — $6.13. Refinanced its 2026 wall out to **2029**; now FCF-positive and posted a GAAP-profitable quarter.\n\n**Bottom line:** CRMT and FFAI are the two names at genuine risk of a mid-2026 filing. Full sourcing and quantitative data points are captured in the structured output.",
